# Day 17 – React Components & Props (Deep Dive)

## React Components

Created reusable components using functions that return JSX. Each component represents a small part of the UI and can be used multiple times throughout the application.

```tsx
function Greetings(props: GreetingProps) {
    return <h2>Hello {props.name} 👋</h2>;
}
```

The component receives data through `props` and displays a dynamic greeting based on the value passed from the parent component.

---

## Props

Defined custom prop types using TypeScript to ensure components receive the correct data.

```tsx
type GreetingProps = {
    name: string;
}
```

Passing props:

```tsx
<Greetings name="Toko" />
<Greetings name="Universe" />
<Greetings name="React" />
```

Each component call passes a different value, allowing the same component to render different content.

